    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_3",
      "description": "This 996-generation Carrera 2 is a mechanically sorted example of Porsche\u2019s analog era. Powered by a 3.4L naturally aspirated flat-six, the engine pulls strongly through the rev range with no evidence of bore scoring. Crucially, the IMS bearing and Rear Main Seal (RMS) have been addressed with documented LN Engineering upgrades. The 6-speed manual transmission is paired with a short-throw kit for precise gear engagement. The chassis has been enhanced with Bilstein B8 dampers and M030-spec sway bars, ensuring flat cornering and excellent feedback through the hydraulic steering rack. While the finish shows minor road-going patina, the drivetrain and suspension geometry are dialed in for the serious enthusiast.",
      "price": 32500.0,
      "reputation": 0.5,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 42
    }
